  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6760.45 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6755 (-7984.5M) and positive gamma ceiling at 6780 (+7352.7M), dealers are in a precarious hedging position where small moves trigger outsized flow responses. The 695% 1-minute GEX surge indicates heavy options activity just hit the tape, likely forcing dealers to rapidly adjust delta hedges as they're currently long gamma but caught in a narrow 25-point range with extreme opposing forces. Key battle zones are the 6755 amplifying support where dealers become aggressive buyers and 6780 resistance where they turn into heavy sellers.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile ping-ponging between 6755 and 6780 until one level breaks decisively.",
